### Uses

Minerals are indispensable to human society, serving a multitude of essential needs. They are the source of [ores](/Ore) for critical components in metal products, forming the backbone of countless commercial [products](/Product_(business)) and [machinery](/Machinery). They are fundamental building materials, forming the basis of [limestone](/Limestone), [marble](/Marble), [granite](/Granite), [gravel](/Gravel), [glass](/Glass), [plaster](/Plaster), and [cement](/Cement). Furthermore, minerals are vital in [fertilizers](/Fertilizer), enriching the soil and enhancing the growth of [agricultural](/Agricultural) crops.

