### Collecting

[Mineral collecting](/Mineral_collecting) is more than a hobby; it's a recreational pursuit deeply intertwined with scientific study, fostering numerous clubs and societies. Prestigious museums worldwide, such as the [Smithsonian](/Smithsonian) [National Museum of Natural History Hall of Geology, Gems, and Minerals](/National_Museum_of_Natural_History), the [Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County](/Natural_History_Museum_of_Los_Angeles_County), the [Carnegie Museum of Natural History](/Carnegie_Museum_of_Natural_History), the [Natural History Museum, London](/Natural_History_Museum,_London), and the private [Mim Mineral Museum](/Mim_Museum) in [Beirut](/Beirut), [Lebanon], showcase impressive collections of mineral specimens, often on permanent display, captivating the public's imagination.

